
 To build C++ apps activating Python :
   cd ./inexlib/exlib/examples/cpp
   ./build -sys_Python hello_py.cpp            # to check Python activation from C++.
   ./build -sys_Python h1d_spy.cpp             # inlib histogram wrapped with swig.
   ./build -sys_Python plotter_spy_screen.cpp  # exlib plotting wrapped with swig.
   ./build -sys_Python mandel_py.cpp           # check calling a C++ function from Python.

 To run :
   ./bin_[gnu,clang]/<app> [options]
   ./bin_gnu/hello_py  # on a Linux.

 Note that the access to Python is in the shell script :
   ./bush/use/Python

